<br>
Before Velious (ie: Old World/Kunark), DS's actually meant something.  They were very powerfull and efficient spells, and with multiple groups tanking mobs they could be a significant factor in combats.<br>
<br>
For example, if a mob hits you for 200 max, and takes 25pts, that's 12.5% (1/8 )  of the mobs damage output turned against themselves.<br>
<br>
However, with Velious and Luclin, we have mobs that hit for 800+, and still only take 25pts damage, which is 0.03% (1/32) of the mobs damage output turned against themselves.<br>
<br>
For Damage Shields to be considered a truely worthy spell line in the high end, they would need to be upgraded considerably.  Verant has shown that they are capable of percentage modifiers in spells, so why not a damage shield that deals 10% (1/10) mob damage back to them?<br>
<br>
Mob hits for 100, takes 10 dmg.<br>
Mob hits for 1000, takes 100 dmg.<br>
Mob hits for 1500, takes 150 dmg.<br>
<br>
The above numbers are all just random figures off the top of my head, but I hope it at least illustrated the idea.<br>
<br>
With the exception casting a DS on the main tank during a fight, damage shields have been made all but redundant, especially group versions.<br>
<br>
And with Warriors having 10k HP, and Verant wanting to make fights challenging without being long battles, mobs will have to have less HP but hit harder, which will make the current damage shields even less effective in comparison.<br>
<br>
45 dmg every time a mob hits the tank for 2k isn't going to be much. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR=#FFFFFF FACE="Comic Sans MS, Sans-Serif, Courier New, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">
