<br>
I think you're very close to what should have been done with a lot of the mob upgrades from Kunark onward.  You can upgrade a mob's melee output by either increasing it's damage or decreasing it's delay.  Damage shields have become diluted in value because most of the melee upgrades for mobs have come in the form of a higher damage number.  There have been delay reductions as well, but as a rule they haven't been the dominate factor in mob upgrades.<br>
<br>
There may actually be a legitimate reason for this other than simply being lazy and not thinking of the consequences for damage shielding classes.  Increasing damage does not consume any more server side resources.  Decreasing delay does.<br>
<br>
One upgrade that I think would be very nice for mages and druids, by the way, that should be possible to implement very nicely with the new &quot;virtual slot&quot; stacking technique that has recently been added, would be for mage and druid damage shields post-50 to stack with one another.  Pre-50 they still wouldn't stack--they're generally pretty strong at those levels anyway--and you wouldn't be able to stack pre-50 with post 50, but post 50 the two classes wouldn't be competing with one another and in combination the damage shields would be strong enough to be valued.<br>
