<br>
If you read my post, you would see I was merely opening a channel for discussion on the topic from comments I have seen on another board.  Please read carefully before you accuse someone else of being ignorant.<br>
<br>
Damage shields do serve a purpose.  The point that was being discussed on the Druid board is that in the days before the &quot;Expansions that broke everything&quot;, damage shields were a useful spell line not only in solo or XP situations, but in raids.<br>
<br>
To this day, they continue to be useful in solo and XP situations.  While they can still contribute to raids they do so nowhere near as significantly, and as such most raiding guilds won't even bother with them.<br>
<br>
